# Backend Python Standards

- Every Python file needs the standard file header with purpose and author `Sreeram`.
- Every class and function needs a docstring explaining what it represents or does and why it exists.
- Every `@function_tool` docstring must include `TOOL`, `Purpose`, `When called`, `Returns`, and `Note: Atomic`.
- Tool inputs and outputs must be typed; in-process tools return ``ToolResultEnvelope`` (see ``backend/schemas.py``); serialize with ``model_dump()`` only at HTTP or persistence boundaries.
- Wrap tool logic in logging and structured error handling that returns `{"error": ..., "result": null}` on failure.
- Use settings or environment variables for configuration; do not hardcode deployment values.
